    <title type="text">New From Trismegistos: The Scholia Minora in Homerum</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div style="font-family: inherit;"><a
      href="http://lists.hum.ku.dk/pipermail/papy/2012-November/001006.html">Trismegistos is
      pleased to announce</a> the s<span style="font-family:
      Gentium;">eventh</span> volume in its series <a
      href="http://www.trismegistos.org/top.php" target="">Trismegistos Online
      Publications</a>: </div><blockquote class="tr_bq"><div style="font-family:
      inherit;"><img alt="http://www.trismegistos.org/img/tm_logo_web2.png"
      src="http://www.trismegistos.org/img/tm_logo_web2.png"
      /></div></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span
      style="font-family: Gentium;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">We are pleased to announce the addition of a new member to the
      <br />Trismegistos Online Publication Series:<br /><br />John Lundon,
      </span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://www.trismegistos.org/dl.php?id=14">The Scholia Minora in Homerum: an
      Alphabetical List, &nbsp;Version 1.0 (November 2012)</a>, KÃ¶ln-Leuven 2012 = TOP 7.
      Pp. 250. ISBN: <br />978-94-9060-407-3.<br /><br />The volume will be of
      interest to students of ancient Homeric </span><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">scholarship, ancient lexicography and paraliterary papyri.<br /><br
      />It contains a short introduction, the full text (lexis + metaphrase +
      </span><span style="font-size: x-small;">any other material) of the entries of all
      the glossaries to the Iliad<span style="color: #0000fe;"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"> </span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span
      style="color: #0000fe;"></span></span>and Odyssey published to date, arranged
      alphabetically by lexis, and a full bibliography. Moreover, each of the entries is linked to
      the Trismegistos database and through it also to the Leuven Database of Ancient
      Books.</span><br /><br /></span></span></blockquote>See all
      volumes available in open access in <a
      href="http://ancientworldonline.blogspot.com/2009/10/open-access-library-trismegistos.html">Trismegistos</a>]]></content>
